The paper deals with equalization and precoding algorithms for wireless systems, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The use of orthogonal frequency-division multiplexing (OFDM) or single-carrier frequency-division multiple access (SC-FDMA) also suggests a possible fit in the Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-category. The paper also proposes novel algorithms that reduce computational complexity, which could be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with massive multi-user (MU) multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) systems, which could be relevant to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
